<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-10-27T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-10-27T12:00:00-05:00" n="616" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d616">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">702.1211/1104: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-10-27T10:00:00-07:00"><hi rend="italic">October 27,
                                        1922—10 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 5:16
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>115. Reference to Oliver Trading Company case, today’s local press
                            published Foreign Office statement to the effect that if the protest
                            stated to have been presented to the Department is not effective Mexican
                            Consulate in New York will be closed.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Summerlin</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>